1
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:21,100
Celeste, it's your fault.

2
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:23,933
Why did you say
that to Ria Campos?

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,733
Why are you blaming me?

4
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:29,500
You almost told the whole world
that father is going to die.

5
00:00:29,567 --> 00:00:31,900
Why are you even saying
that I'm the liar?

6
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:33,533
You're the liar.

7
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,100
If you didn't make me haggard

8
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,400
and said that father had
an emergency, this and that.

9
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:41,233
I shouldn't have gone all
the way here in Sorsogon

10
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:43,433
and wouldn't end up
in this mess.

11
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:46,200
I just actually have
to stay here

12
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:50,400
for a couple of days
or maybe weeks.

13
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:52,767
You know, to have that
doting daughter image

14
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:56,300
because it's not good
to see me staying in the hotel.

15
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:58,400
So I'll just have to
stay here for a while.

16
00:00:58,467 --> 00:01:02,100
It's an honor to be doing this
with all of you

17
00:01:02,167 --> 00:01:04,833
here in Sorsogon.

18
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:07,100
So I hope you can give me
another chance

19
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,400
to correct my mistakes.

20
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:11,067
Thank you so much.

21
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:14,333
Like I said, I made
a mistake before

22
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:18,400
and I really hope that
I can live up to the ideals

23
00:01:18,467 --> 00:01:20,933
of a true Sorsogueno.

24
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,933
What did I deserve
to have a smart

25
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,300
and a charming woman like you?

26
00:01:24,367 --> 00:01:25,967
You're sweet-talking again.

27
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:29,533
What a pity my schedules
are piled up.

28
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:32,133
Because I was enjoying spending
time with your family

29
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,333
in Sorsogon.

30
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,567
You know, Love, it's okay.

31
00:01:34,633 --> 00:01:37,767
You don't have to feel
obligated to be with my family.

32
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:39,033
You've done enough.

33
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:42,667
Well, the truth is, just
can't wait to see you again.

34
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:45,333
Wow, how sweet.

35
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:48,100
You were never that
romantic with me.

36
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:49,233
Hello, Aurelia.

37
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:52,733
Celeste, just in time,
you're here.

38
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,900
I will introduce you

39
00:01:53,967 --> 00:01:56,833
to the coordinator
for your community service.

40
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:59,333
- Who is it?
- You're wrong, Mayor.

41
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:02,867
It's Celeste, not Celes-te.

42
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:06,200
I asked Mikoy to report
about your community service.

43
00:02:06,267 --> 00:02:09,867
To be sure that you will
take it seriously, Celeste.

44
00:02:09,933 --> 00:02:11,533
I mean, Celeste.

45
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:27,600
Oh my God, this can't be.

46
00:02:27,667 --> 00:02:28,933
What's happening?

47
00:02:30,467 --> 00:02:31,933
I'm having acid reflux.

48
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:35,600
What is this?

49
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:36,700
My God.

50
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:41,633
Celeste?

51
00:02:42,933 --> 00:02:45,833
Mikoy.

52
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:47,333
I hope we won't
have a problem.

53
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:51,600
Why would we
have a problem?

54
00:02:51,667 --> 00:02:52,667
Just do what is right.

55
00:02:52,733 --> 00:02:55,833
I'll be fair with what
I'll tell the court.

56
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,733
Thank you so much that you
agreed to have

57
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:01,767
the community service be
documented to promote Sorsogon.

58
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:03,867
You know, with your social
media presence,

59
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:06,367
it will help a lot
in the tourism of Sorsogon.

60
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:11,367
You know, that's the reason why
I stayed here.

61
00:03:11,433 --> 00:03:16,733
Instead of any capitalist that
will benefit from my abilities,

62
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:21,033
I'd rather stay here, right,
to help our townspeople.

63
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:25,267
So you're saying that
those who leave are bad

64
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:27,967
because they have big dreams
that they won't achieve

65
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:30,600
here in Sorsogon. Are you saying
they are selfish?

66
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:32,467
No, that's not what I meant.

67
00:03:34,067 --> 00:03:37,333
- My point is...
- You don't have to explain.

68
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,033
So what do I need to do?

69
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:43,033
I mean, tell me my obligations
for the community service...

70
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:47,867
that I need do for our town
so we can move on.

71
00:03:47,933 --> 00:03:49,633
Our town?

72
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:52,067
Whatever.

73
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:53,700
Okay, let's start
your obligation.

74
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,667
Yeah, okay.

75
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:57,167
Here.

76
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:35,767
I must admit, I didn't expect
that Celeste is media savvy.

77
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:37,400
I was impressed that
she was able to get out

78
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:40,000
of the trouble
she got herself into.

79
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:41,800
That's the problem with you.

80
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:45,333
You keep on underestimating her.

81
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,633
Next time, she won't
be that lucky.

82
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:50,467
What makes you think
there's a next time?

83
00:04:50,533 --> 00:04:53,633
Dad, she's a fraud.

84
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:55,000
Do you really know her?

85
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:00,733
I didn't know that
she's from Sorsogon.

86
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,067
I didn't even know that
she has a family there.

87
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:08,967
And is her Dad even dying
or it's just one of her dramas?

88
00:05:09,033 --> 00:05:10,267
Tiff, that's enough.

89
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:12,233
No, Dad, because from what
I can sense...

90
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:17,300
your fiancé is hiding so many
skeletons in her closet.

91
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:20,233
And that viral video
that we saw...

92
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:22,333
that's just a preview
of who she really is.

93
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,100
You know, Dad, one day,

94
00:05:25,167 --> 00:05:27,533
you will know the true color
of that woman.

95
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,867
And you won't like it.

96
00:05:28,933 --> 00:05:31,133
I said enough!

97
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:34,633
The day you were born
was my proudest moment.

98
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:36,200
But now...

99
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:38,233
you're such
a disappointment.

100
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:41,100
Tonito, you're overreacting.

101
00:05:46,233 --> 00:05:48,733
Really, Dad?

102
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,833
Do you think I'm proud
of our family?

103
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:55,100
We keep on having dinner and
lunch as if nothing is wrong.

104
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:59,800
As if we're whole, as if
we're happy, as if this is real.

105
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,233
But that's not the truth
because this is just a façade.

106
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:10,467
Because we are not happy,
we are not whole.

107
00:06:10,533 --> 00:06:11,500
This is not real...

108
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:16,400
because you gave up on us.

109
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,633
You gave up on me and mommy.

110
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,533
And I'm sorry...

111
00:06:26,967 --> 00:06:28,800
I'm sorry
if I'm a disappointment.

112
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,633
But you giving up on us...

113
00:06:35,567 --> 00:06:37,267
is my greatest pain.

114
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,367
- Excuse me.
- Tiffany...

115
00:06:43,433 --> 00:06:44,700
Tiffany, stop!

116
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:50,300
Oh, Tonito.

117
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:53,833
Tiff!

118
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,033
Vivian.

119
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:09,467
Is she here?

120
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:11,833
I know she goes here

121
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:14,100
whenever she and her dad
are fighting.

122
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:17,600
What happened to her and Tonito?

123
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:20,100
They fought again
about Celeste.

124
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:22,000
She was here earlier.

125
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:23,733
But she left already.

126
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:26,733
She said she will be
in school with friends.

127
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,167
If she comes home here later,

128
00:07:29,233 --> 00:07:31,167
please tell her
to answer my call.

129
00:07:34,933 --> 00:07:36,367
Join me for tea.

130
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:40,267
Don't tell me you will avoid it?

131
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:56,100
Thank you.

132
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:17,900
Wow...

133
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,133
impressive.

134
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,900
This is not
how I remember this library.

135
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:27,533
You're like that.

136
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,533
There are a lot of things
that you don't want to remember.

137
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:34,767
You know, the truth is,
nothing much has changed here.

138
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:40,200
Well, a lot has changed.

139
00:08:41,533 --> 00:08:42,500
Me...

140
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:45,933
you.

141
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:49,700
But many things
can't be changed.

142
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:54,300
Like the memories,
we can't change that.

143
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,000
Do you know this is
where I first met you?

144
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,600
If I wasn't there that day,
for sure you bumped your head.

145
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,167
You made it up.

146
00:09:45,467 --> 00:09:49,067
Well, if I remember clearly,
that's not what I recall.

147
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,933
Hey, why did you dive there?

148
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,233
How was it?

149
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:19,733
How many fishes did you get?

150
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,567
That's impossible.

151
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:36,367
That's it. That's what happened.

152
00:10:36,467 --> 00:10:37,533
I'm sure you're just embarrassed

153
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,100
that's why you changed the story
throughout the years.

154
00:10:40,167 --> 00:10:42,800
But that's what I remember.

155
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:45,767
No.

156
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:51,400
What I remember is the right
version of how we've met.

157
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:52,867
So...

158
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:55,867
you brought me here
to argue with the version

159
00:10:55,933 --> 00:10:56,967
that you know?

160
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,300
What is that?

161
00:11:14,367 --> 00:11:16,167
It makes me feel itchy.

162
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:17,333
Sorry, it's dusty.

163
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:20,567
Is that for real?

164
00:11:21,733 --> 00:11:22,700
Are you sure?

165
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,800
This is still okay.
This is what we use

166
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:27,733
whenever I cover festivals.

167
00:11:29,767 --> 00:11:31,867
- This is still working.
- So wait, this is what mayor

168
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:34,000
was referring to
when he said that

169
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:35,700
he has a documentary crew
using that?

170
00:11:35,767 --> 00:11:36,700
Basically, it's you and...

171
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:39,033
the camera.

172
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:40,500
We're not a big city.

173
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:44,800
This is still okay.
It's still working.

174
00:11:44,867 --> 00:11:46,600
No, that's okay.

175
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:50,933
I cannot appear in a low-budget
film. It's off-branding.

176
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,367
I'd rather use my phone
than that.

177
00:11:53,433 --> 00:11:54,467
This is high definition.

178
00:11:56,533 --> 00:11:57,833
Are you done insulting?

179
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:59,500
Can we do a camera test?

180
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:00,667
Test? Trash.

181
00:12:00,733 --> 00:12:02,800
No, my gosh. I can't.

182
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:05,000
I'm just going to call
my secretary.

183
00:12:05,067 --> 00:12:08,800
And I'm going to ask her
to send a film crew here.

184
00:12:08,867 --> 00:12:09,900
We have no budget.

185
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:12,533
We have no money
to pay for your crew.

186
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,367
Am I asking for payment?

187
00:12:14,467 --> 00:12:16,367
Don't worry,
I'll pay for the cost.

188
00:12:18,267 --> 00:12:20,500
And besides,
just think about it as me...

189
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:25,400
giving back to my beloved
Sorsogon.

190
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:29,100
So that people won't judge me
anymore that I left

191
00:12:29,167 --> 00:12:30,400
because I have big dreams.

192
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:36,233
Anyway, if that's what you will
use, people might be discouraged

193
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:38,533
to come here
because it's a low budget.

194
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,833
I mean they won't be enticed.

195
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:42,333
They might think that
it's a home video

196
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:45,267
of the Blair Witch Project.

197
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,767
All right, so I'll see you.

198
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:52,333
Yeah.

199
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:53,367
And oh...

200
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:01,500
this might be our last project
together.

201
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:03,767
So...

202
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:04,933
let's do our best.

203
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:07,800
We don't want to end up
as failures

204
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:10,367
just like the two of us.

205
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:37,333
Oh man, this fashion designer
is all over my feed.

206
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,367
Hey, you know this Celeste,
right?

207
00:13:39,433 --> 00:13:41,233
Isn't she dating your dad?

208
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,933
Babe, do you think
I really want to talk about

209
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,867
who my dad is dating?

210
00:13:47,933 --> 00:13:50,433
Oh. Okay, I'm sorry.

211
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:54,500
Okay...

212
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:59,667
what do you want us
to talk about today?

213
00:13:59,733 --> 00:14:02,233
The proposal of our project
presentation

214
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:07,200
or we gossip about whoever
is trending in social media.

215
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:10,800
Oh by the way, Tiff,
Clau showed me the email.

216
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:12,300
And I saw your proposal.

217
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:13,867
I think it's awesome.

218
00:14:13,933 --> 00:14:15,667
Yeah, I like it.

219
00:14:15,733 --> 00:14:19,400
And about the out of town trip,

220
00:14:19,467 --> 00:14:21,267
I think it would be very fun

221
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:25,167
and I hope you are also
my groupmates.

222
00:14:25,233 --> 00:14:26,533
Just relax, Bro.

223
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,800
You're not in our group.

224
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,633
Okay.

225
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:33,300
Clau...

226
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:35,833
you're showing emails now?

227
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:37,700
No, what's with you?

228
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:39,700
It's a brilliant test, right?

229
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:43,833
Imagine a music and
arts festival in Albay.

230
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:47,967
In a backdrop of majestic
Mayon celebrating local music,

231
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:50,600
culture, and the arts, right?

232
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:55,267
And if you guys pull this off,
Albay can be similar to Cebu.

233
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:59,567
And maybe it can be
the next Coachella.

234
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:04,000
So what will be my
and Clau's contribution?

235
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:06,933
Well, I can take charge
of everything.

236
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,400
I can prepare scripts
in the presentation

237
00:15:09,467 --> 00:15:12,200
for our professor's possible
questions.

238
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:14,200
And guys...

239
00:15:14,267 --> 00:15:18,300
please memorize it
so it will look like

240
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:19,700
you have a contribution here.

241
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:26,000
I'm so excited for Albay.

242
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:31,767
So Clau, in what stage of dating
are you now with David?

243
00:15:35,667 --> 00:15:37,167
Wait, I have to go
to the comfort room.

244
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:38,567
Comfort room?

245
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:46,367
- David!
- So David.

246
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:49,500
So David, what stage?

247
00:15:49,567 --> 00:15:50,833
Honestly...

248
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:53,633
- Guys, you really want to know?
- Yeah.

249
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:55,467
It's kinda complicated.

250
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:56,367
Complicated?

251
00:15:56,433 --> 00:15:59,533
Why?

252
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:02,900
Vivian, you have to understand.

253
00:16:02,967 --> 00:16:05,367
Tonito's decision
to marry Celeste

254
00:16:05,433 --> 00:16:08,433
has a big impact on Tiffany.

255
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:15,467
Tiffany is a smart kid
but she's still is just a kid.

256
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:19,967
Well, I will play the role
of a supportive Auntie.

257
00:16:21,767 --> 00:16:24,100
But it's your problem
as her mother.

258
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:29,667
Which begs me the question,
what happened to you and Tonito?

259
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:32,000
You were the one who told me...

260
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:37,333
that a marriage is like
a business transaction.

261
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,300
And you are absolutely right.

262
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:45,100
Sometimes you gain,
sometimes you lose.

263
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:48,367
In my case with Tonito,
no matter what we do,

264
00:16:48,433 --> 00:16:51,600
it's unfortunate that our love
failed miserably.

265
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:56,167
Because our priorities in life
are really different.

266
00:16:57,200 --> 00:17:02,300
I must admit,
I was also selfish.

267
00:17:02,367 --> 00:17:05,367
In my desire to conquer
the world...

268
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:09,500
I took him for granted.

269
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:13,533
There is nothing wrong
with being number one, Aurelia.

270
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:19,200
But as with any successful
business transaction,

271
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:22,100
there should be a compromise.

272
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:24,500
And that's what you
and Tonito failed to do.

273
00:17:26,133 --> 00:17:29,667
You know, compromising
doesn't mean that you win over

274
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:33,533
the other or one is right
and one is wrong.

275
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:36,700
It means that you value
your relationship

276
00:17:36,767 --> 00:17:38,067
more than your ego.

277
00:17:39,133 --> 00:17:41,967
I have learned my lesson
the hard way

278
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:47,600
because Tonito and I let
our egos prevail.

279
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:53,300
Even our daughter got involved
in our wrong decisions in life.

280
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:58,800
Vivian, if only I could turn
back time.

281
00:17:58,867 --> 00:18:01,867
I will never let go of Tonito.

282
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:07,467
I wish I would've
humbled myself.

283
00:18:09,567 --> 00:18:10,533
I should've...

284
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,900
sacrificed more.

285
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:16,267
But you didn't do that, Aurelia.

286
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:22,600
Look what happened to your
family with Tonito, to Tiffany.

287
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:29,000
You didn't fight hard
for your love, for your family.

288
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:31,667
And that makes me
feel really bad.

289
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:32,700
Vivian...

290
00:18:32,767 --> 00:18:34,433
No, that's true.

291
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:38,700
I'm your matchmaker.

292
00:18:41,133 --> 00:18:44,233
And I won't deny it there
are real advantages in business.

293
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:46,833
Because your family has been
our business partner

294
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:48,367
for a long time.

295
00:18:48,433 --> 00:18:51,600
But believe it or not Aurelia,
I sincerely believed

296
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:53,133
that you and Tonito
looked good together.

297
00:18:56,067 --> 00:19:00,733
But I guess I was wrong,
a costly mistake.

298
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:02,600
Because in the process...

299
00:19:02,667 --> 00:19:05,033
I might have ruined your life.

300
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:09,700
All the hurt that you feel now,
the hurt that Tiffany feels,

301
00:19:09,767 --> 00:19:11,967
it's all my fault.

302
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:16,233
Vivian, don't say that.

303
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:19,700
I willingly made
that decision myself.

304
00:19:19,767 --> 00:19:23,200
No one forced me
and to tell you the truth,

305
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,600
I had high hopes as well.

306
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:31,433
What do you mean?

307
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:37,300
I will not marry just
because you want it

308
00:19:37,367 --> 00:19:41,800
or because it's good
for my parent's business.

309
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:47,967
I'm not dumb who simply follows
the order of others.

310
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,267
I genuinely love Tonito...

311
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,467
and most of all...

312
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:01,233
he's not difficult to love.

313
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:28,533
Your coffee is delicious, Love.

314
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,067
It's a good morning.

315
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:37,933
Oh, that's a lot.

316
00:20:39,567 --> 00:20:41,033
- Hey, Sebastian.
- Good morning, Mother, Father.

317
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:43,733
- Good morning.
- Earlier, I was in a bad mood

318
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:45,933
because Celeste is staying here.

319
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:49,033
But if because of her every day
is like a fiesta...

320
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,567
she is very much welcome
with me.

321
00:20:53,933 --> 00:20:55,400
Stop it.

322
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:57,433
You should wash your face first
before you eat.

323
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:58,500
Okay.

324
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:03,600
Love...

325
00:21:03,667 --> 00:21:06,033
aren't we being
obvious here?

326
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:08,400
Isn't this a bit too much?

327
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:11,767
Isn't it obvious that
we're wooing her?

328
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:15,133
Isn't there a saying
that the best way

329
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:18,100
to someone's heart
is through their stomach?

330
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:19,200
Let's try this.

331
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:21,167
Your daughter's heart
will eventually soften.

332
00:21:28,933 --> 00:21:31,233
Celeste, good morning.

333
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:33,433
Why are you wearing that?

334
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,900
You have community service.

335
00:21:34,967 --> 00:21:37,467
Won't you have a hard time
with that outfit of yours?

336
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:39,667
Your outfit is beautiful,
Celeste.

337
00:21:39,733 --> 00:21:42,933
It looks expensive
but your father is right.

338
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:44,800
It will only get dirty
where you will go.

339
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,167
Don't worry about it.

340
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:49,400
We have a film crew
that's waiting for us.

341
00:21:49,467 --> 00:21:52,067
So, you know, it will be good
promoting Sorsogon,

342
00:21:52,133 --> 00:21:54,600
everything is on brand
and it's also good for my image.

343
00:21:58,067 --> 00:21:59,367
What did she say?

344
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:00,500
You should eat first.

345
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:01,567
You have a long day ahead.

346
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:03,467
It's better if you start
with a full stomach.

347
00:22:03,533 --> 00:22:04,300
Come on.

348
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:05,800
It's okay.

349
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:07,167
I don't eat breakfast.

350
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:09,700
I'm on eternal
intermittent fasting.

351
00:22:09,767 --> 00:22:12,000
It's quite healthy,
you should try it.

352
00:22:12,067 --> 00:22:13,867
Is that so?

353
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:14,900
Just take this.

354
00:22:17,767 --> 00:22:19,767
Maybe you eat lunch.

355
00:22:19,833 --> 00:22:21,800
Here...

356
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:23,233
I prepared lunch for you.

357
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:28,867
Sorry, I don't eat carbs.

358
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:31,333
It becomes sugar.

359
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,667
Thank you.

360
00:22:32,733 --> 00:22:34,800
You guys have a good day.

361
00:22:34,867 --> 00:22:35,833
Bye, Celeste.

362
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:51,500
Love...

363
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:54,267
I'll eat that.

364
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:55,300
Okay.

365
00:22:56,833 --> 00:23:00,367
Wow, this is your delicious
adobo.

366
00:23:00,433 --> 00:23:04,567
Adobo with shrimp paste
and with coconut milk.

367
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:06,200
Go ahead, you eat.

368
00:23:06,267 --> 00:23:07,567
I will.

369
00:23:07,633 --> 00:23:08,967
I really like this.

370
00:23:11,467 --> 00:23:16,900
With one of the most active
volcanoes serving as a backdrop,

371
00:23:16,967 --> 00:23:21,233
Albay will be the next melting
pot of culture, arts,

372
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:25,833
and music, exploding
in artistry.

373
00:23:25,933 --> 00:23:28,467
Rivaling with Coachella,
Burning Man,

374
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:32,167
and any other festivals
in the whole wide world.

375
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:35,333
Please welcome,
Lava Land Festival.

376
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:38,033
Next slide, please.

377
00:23:39,633 --> 00:23:42,000
All right,
thank you, Ms. Tiffany.

378
00:23:42,067 --> 00:23:43,800
I think this is a great
presentation.

379
00:23:43,867 --> 00:23:46,600
But we have one problem.

380
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,167
What's the problem, Sir?

381
00:23:52,233 --> 00:23:56,867
Well, one of your classmates
presented the exact same thing.

382
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:58,567
And since their group
was ahead,

383
00:23:58,633 --> 00:24:00,900
you need to change
your presentation.

384
00:24:00,967 --> 00:24:02,033
Right, Cynthia?

385
00:24:14,167 --> 00:24:17,133
When we arrive
at the first location

386
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,767
you should start the shoot.

387
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:20,233
The place where we will go
is beautiful.

388
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,600
It's not yet that popular

389
00:24:21,667 --> 00:24:23,767
but we from Sorsogon
are proud of it.

390
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:25,467
We'll just follow you, Sir,
and we'll take care of it.

391
00:24:25,533 --> 00:24:26,767
Whatever videos that we have,

392
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:29,167
we'll send it over
to our editor in Manila.

393
00:24:29,267 --> 00:24:30,900
Okay. Let's wait for Celeste.

394
00:24:30,967 --> 00:24:32,000
Okay.

395
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:33,833
Stop acting as if
you're the most beautiful

396
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:37,433
and intelligent because clearly,
it's not you.

397
00:25:37,533 --> 00:25:38,767
You must be ready.

398
00:25:38,833 --> 00:25:40,633
Do not wait
for the perfect moment.

399
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:43,067
You're the last person
I want to see.

400
00:25:43,133 --> 00:25:44,933
The face of my ex-husband.

401
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,033
Are you torturing me
or punishing me?

402
00:25:47,100 --> 00:25:50,367
Sorry but just because you will
promote Sorsogon,

403
00:25:50,433 --> 00:25:52,500
it doesn't mean you will not do
your community service properly.

404
00:25:52,567 --> 00:25:53,733
Of course, you still need
to do that.

405
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:55,900
So what is this?
Your "so I told you" moment?

406
00:25:55,967 --> 00:26:04,767
Why can't you give the love
you're giving her to me?

407
00:26:04,833 --> 00:26:06,500
Here is the other one.

408
00:26:06,567 --> 00:26:07,900
It's an inconvenience...

409
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,333
but I'll take it.

410
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:13,200
Have a good day.

411
00:26:13,267 --> 00:26:16,167
Everyone is talking about
your stepmother, Tiffany.

412
00:26:17,367 --> 00:26:19,300
She got some crazy
videos in Sorsogon.

413
00:26:19,367 --> 00:26:22,300
Oh my, what's this?

414
00:26:22,367 --> 00:26:25,433
Just think that
you stepped on a...

415
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:27,467
melted grated coconut.

416
00:26:27,533 --> 00:26:29,767
Don't even try to find out
what that is because it's gross.

417
00:26:29,833 --> 00:26:33,100
Possibly we can mount
a better event in Sorsogon.

418
00:26:33,167 --> 00:26:34,400
What do you think, Tiff?

419
00:26:34,467 --> 00:26:38,600
If you guys are sure...

420
00:26:38,667 --> 00:26:39,367
- why not.
- Wait, it's like

421
00:26:39,433 --> 00:26:42,500
it's getting into the plastic.

422
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:44,033
What will I do?

423
00:26:47,133 --> 00:26:48,767
It smells awful.
